<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6193138-skyqueen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1315544691i/6193138._UX100_CR0,3,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6193138-skyqueen">Skyqueen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Serious teens, young adults, adults, and seniors ...who have actually lived it! So it will be a pseudo-memoire for them. An unadulterated look at hist<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Serious teens, young adults, adults, and seniors ...who have actually lived it! So it will be a pseudo-memoire for them. An unadulterated look at historical life in the poor South for which, sadly, not much has changed. When I actually visited the Montgomery area back in the late 90's, my impression was that it was 20 years behind. However, I thoroughly enjoyed it, for as much of the writing style as the truth. People like Dolly Parton grew up in this general area and type of life too. As well as Elvis, Jerry Lee Lewis, and Jimmy Swaggart. It doesn't hurt to expose yourself to the diversity of our great nation.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
